				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I'm taking a short break from our book marketing series today to share a little more information about the HorrorSelfies.com campaign from The Horror Writers Association. (Disclosure: I was involved with the campaign and built the site for it.)</p>
<p>What I didn't mention in my previous post is that by submitting your very own horror selfies promoting literacy and the horror genre, you'll be entered into a contest. The prize? More than 50 signed horror books! Yep. That's right. The winner receives the entire collection of signed editions. And the list is continually growing. If you're a horror fan, you don't want to miss this opportunity.</p>
<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-29318" src="http://allindiewriters.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/horrorselfies.jpg" alt="Horror Selfies" width="600" height="429" /></p>
<h2>The Books</h2>
<p>You can find a list of the current books up for grabs in this contest, including books from Peter Straub and Ramsey Campbell, <a href="http://horrorselfies.com/full-list-contest-books/">here</a>.</p>
<h2>How to Enter</h2>
<ul>
<li>Take a selfie with a sign (paper, white board, writing on your hand, digital text added to a photo, etc.) promoting literacy, reading or writing horror, or your favorite library.</li>
<li>Optimize your photo so it's less than 100kb in size (600px wide is ideal).</li>
<li><a href="http://horrorselfies.com/submit/">Submit your horror selfie</a> before November 6th.</li>
</ul>
<p>Please read the full <a href="http://horrorselfies.com/submission-guidelines/">submission guidelines</a> before submitting your selfie.</p>
